Q5.Char minimum value : -128

Explaination :Char occupies only one byte but can take both positive and negative values thus its range is -128 to 127. 
1 byte = 8 bits = 2^8 characters.
Thus half of these are positive while the rest are negative. Hence the negative characters are (2^8)/2 = 128, thereby making the minimum equal to -128.

