Q6.Char maximum value : 127

Explaination :Char occupies only one byte but can take both positive and negative values thus its range is -128 to 127. 
1 byte = 8 bits = 2^8 characters.
Thus half of these are positive while the rest are negative. Hence the positive characters are (2^8)/2 - 1 = 127, thereby making the maximum equal to 127. Zero is also a part of the positive characters , thus the maximum is 127 and not 128.

