Q7.Signed short minimum value : -32768

Explaination: Signed short occupies 2 bytes and can take both positive and negative values, thus its range is -32768 to 32767
2 bytes = 16 bits = (2^16) characters
Thus half of these are positive while the rest are negative. Hence the negative  characters are (2^16)/2 = 32768, thereby making the minimum equal to -32768.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q8.Signed short maximum value : 32767

Explaination: Signed short occupies 2 bytes and can take both positive and negative values, thus its range is -32768 to 32767
2 bytes = 16 bits = (2^16) characters
Thus half of these are positive while the rest are negative. Hence the positive characters are (2^16)/2 = 32768, thereby making the maximum  equal to 32767 after including zero.

