Q9. Unsigned short minimum value : 0

Explaination: The unsigned short occupies two bytes but can take only positive values. Thus its range is from 0 to 65535.
2 byte = 16 bits = 2^16 characters.
As the unsigned short takes only positive values the minimum automatically become 0.

