Q10.Unsigned short maximum value : 65535

Explaination: Unsigned short occupies 2 bytes and can take only positive values, thus its range is 0 to 65535
2 bytes = 16 bits = (2^16) characters
As all of these are positive,  Hence the positive characters are (2^16) =65536 , thereby making the maximum  equal to 65535 after including zero.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Q11.Signed int minimum value: -2147483648

Explaination: Signed int occupies 4 bytes and can take both positive and negative values, thus its range is -2147483648 to 2147483647
4 bytes = 32 bits = (2^32) characters
Thus half of these are positive while the rest are negative. Hence the negative  characters are (2^32)/2 = 2147483648, thereby making the minimum equal to -2147483648.

