Q15. Signed long minimum value: -9223372036854775808

Explaination: Signed long occupies 8 bytes and can take both positive and negative values, thus its range is -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807
8 bytes = 64 bits = (2^64) characters
Thus half of these are positive while the rest are negative. Hence the negative  characters are (2^64)/2 = 9223372036854775808, thereby making the minimum equal to -9223372036854775808.

